{"word":"θαρσύνω","slug":"θαρσύνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θαρσύνω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>Causal of <el>θαρσέω</el>, <i>to encourage, cheer</i>, <el>θάρσυνον</el> (aor1 <a href='S:imperative mood'>imperat.</a>) <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>θαρσύνεσκε</el> (ionic <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>) <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; so <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> <el>θάρσυνε</el> <i>be of good courage</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}